Logan, Martin  | Engineering Alumni | University of Illinois at Chicago                     It all starts with a single spark         Skip to the content of this page ,  the main menu , the site search form , the site home page .        UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni     Search the site     Toggle Menu      Search                  UIC Logo          Engineering Alumni      Engineering Alumni   Main Menu    News    Expand News menu           Dean's List    RISE Magazine         Events    Expand Events menu           Upcoming Events         Get Involved    Expand Get Involved menu           Join us on LinkedIn    Become a Mentor    Volunteer    Engineer your own involvement    Honor a Professor         Awards    Expand Awards menu           2019 Alumni Award Honorees    2018 Alumni Award Honorees    2017 Alumni Award Honorees         Give    Contact     Eyebrow menu    College of Engineering    Engineering Career Center    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map       Search                           Martin  Logan  OUTSTANDING ACHIEVEMENT AWARD  BS ’01 | Computer Science                About   Martin Logan is a product development expert specializing in creating high performance product development organizations. He is recognized for his outstanding ability to manage teams and overhaul processes. Before joining Guaranteed Rate, Logan led the gallery software development team for the Amazon Kindle Fire and Fire TV. He is credited with launching all of the client software for the Amazon Cloud Drive platform. At Orbitz, Logan ran all of SEO and merchandising. He built its entire mobile practice from the ground up winning Orbitz a place in Apple’s App Hall of Fame. Logan joined Guaranteed Rate in 2014 and immediately made it his mission to disrupt the mortgage industry by taking a paper-based system into the digital age. He developed The World’s First Digital Mortgage, making Guaranteed Rate the first to bring such a system to market. Then, he developed the Intuitive Loan Finder, the first intuitive, price transparent, loan shopping engine. These accomplishments have earned him industry-wide recognition. Winner of the American Business Awards Silver Stevie for Information Technology Executive of the Year in 2016, Logan continues to bring future technology into the now. He is a 2015 Built in Chicago Moxie Award finalist for CTO of the Year. A published author, Logan co-wrote the well-respected computer programing book “Erlang and OTP in Action.” Logan holds a bachelor’s degree in computer science from UIC.                    UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni       Contact   851 S. Morgan - SEO Rm. 811  Phone: 3129969422  MWilli60@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 